'''Vikna Wind Farm''' ({{lang-no|Vikna vindmøllepark}}) is located on Husfjellet, just west of the village of [[Garstad]] on the island [[Mellom-Vikna]] in the municipality of [[Vikna]] in [[Trøndelag]] county, [[Norway]]. The [[wind farm]] consists of five [[wind turbines]], with an installed capacity of {{convert|2.2|MW}} (calculated as 3 x 0.4&nbsp;MW + 2 x 0.5&nbsp;MW), with an average annual production of {{convert|5.8|GWh}}. The wind farm began operation in 1991 and is owned by [[Nord-Trøndelag Elektrisitetsverk]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nte.no/index.php/vindkraft|title=Vindkraft|language=Norwegian |accessdate=2011-10-03|publisher=NTE}}</ref>
